The paper deals with object recognition and convolutional neural networks, which are primarily studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses knowledge transfer and domain adaptation, which are topics commonly studied in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Finally, the paper explores how to make CNNs more efficient, which is a topic that falls under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
